author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: High schools: Naples boys roll past South Seneca
text: Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 10:32 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. The Naples boys soccer team maintained its unbeaten season with a 6-0 Finger Lakes West victory over South Seneca on Wednesday. Zach Dormer scored two goals and assisted on another, and Conrad Rathbun also scored twice for the Big Green (7-0-2, 9-0-3). Seth Price and Scott Emmons added the other goals for Naples, which got seven saves from Jake Chapman. Skyler Rasmussen made five saves for South Seneca (3-4-2, 4-5-2). Naples was led by Zach Dormer who had 2 goals and an assist and Conrad Rathbun who had two goals. Also scoring for Naples were Seth price and Scott Emmons. Jake Chapman had 7 saves for Naples earning the win. Skyler Rasmussen had 5 saves for SS. Bloomfield 4, Honeoye 1 Wyatt Conklin, Jimmy Stahl, Jimmy Hart and Christian Eveleigh each scored for Bloomfield (5-2-1, 8-3-1). Bryce Beechler made six saves. Matt Pestle scored for Honeoye (2-6-1, 2-9-1). H-AC 6, Midlakes 0 Ben Frennette scored two goals and assisted on one for Harley-Allendale Columbia (7-1, 8-3). Mateo Alexander also scored, and Zack Kaufmann made one save. Josh Tubbs made 15 saves for Midakes (1-9). Girls soccer Kaci Messier and Kate Leonard scored goals for Victor (5-2-3). Boys golf Nate Longbine led Honeoye (10-2) with a 42 at Old Hickory. Girls tennis Palmyra-Macedon 5, Newark 0 The first doubles team of Anna Oâ€™Donnell and Marietta Koeberle defeated Ashley Porter and Kaitlyn Pieters, 6-0, 6-1, to help Palmyra-Macedon wrap up its regular season with an 11-0 record. Erin Graham, Cara Graham and Shelby Hutton recorded wins in singles matches for Pal-Mac. Girls swimming Newark 105, North Rose-Wolcott-Red Creek 78 Ali House led Newark with her win in the diving event, setting a Finger Lakes League record with a score of 324.55. The score also is a North Rose-Wolcott pool record and a Newark school record. House also won the 100 free (1:03.98) and was on the winning 200 medley relay team for the Reds. Emma Correia won the 200 free (2:20.21) and the 500 free (6:15.85) for Newark. Tuesday Boys volleyball Webster Thomas 3, Canandaigua 1 Max Colcord had eight kills for Canandaigua (2-6) and Kody Miles had three aces against Thomas, which won by scores of 25-21, 25-12, 25-27 and 28-26. For Webster Thomas (5-4), Chris McKrell had 17 kills and eight assists, and Justin Spiegel 10 kills and six blocks. By Messenger Post
